ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It would be a difficult class if you don't already have a background in computer science, math or philosophical logic. Can be a very enjoyable course, but it is necessary to spend a lot of time on the homework and to start working diligently from the very beginning of the semester.

This is a great class. It starts simple, but gets quite complicated around two-thirds of the way through. The professor is funny and fun to listen to. Overall, I'd recommend it for anyone who likes to think deeply and mathematically.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Great introduction into some interesting issues in the philosophy logic about the nature of formal systems and our analysis of them.
